Text: Welcome back to my garden. The new buds are sprouting in glorious shades of green, so please stay and enjoy the vista for as long as you like.
If you're traveling to Urqopacha, might I interest you in an alpaca? They're as reliable as they are fashionable─Wuk Lamat herself rode one during the rite of succession, you know.
Alpacas will carry you safely, be it in temporary evacuation or upon the long road to Urqopacha.
Our alpacas are ready for anything. There's no telling what the coming days might hold, but insofar as you need swift and safe travel to Urqopacha, you can rely on us.
The enemy may have retreated, but the fight is far from over. If you're headed to Urqopacha, take care.
Peace has returned at last. We have alpacas standing by to facilitate your greater journey across Tural. First stop─Urqopacha!
Today I'll raise a cup in honor of the Third Promise─or should I say, our new Vow of Resolve. And, yes, I'll be cracking open that jug of premium mezcal!
I heard about what happened in Tuliyollal. After what Zoraal Ja did, I can't believe I ever supported him...
I'm glad to hear the city survived the invasion, albeit not unscathed. To think I ever believed Zoraal Ja worthy of the throne...

You remember that mezcal Wuk Lamat traded me for a saddle? I finished off the jug the day she was named Dawnservant. Ah, it might just have been the finest drink I've ever had the pleasure to imbibe...
They sell mezcal directly from the distillery here. If you're a spirit drinker, I encourage you to give it a taste.
I was in Tuliyollal during the ascension ceremony, treating everyone to a banquet at my restaurant. The crowd was all smiles, full of good food and mezcal!
I was here making a purchase when my restaurant in Tuliyollal was apparently damaged in an explosion. I could've been killed...
When the invaders attacked the city, one of the buildings they hit was my restaurant... How am I ever to rebuild my business?
My restaurant was damaged during the invasion, so the Pelu have offered to help me out until I get back on my feet.
For starters, the distillers here have agreed to sell me mezcal at a heavily discounted price. Coming from these habitual dealmakers, it is a kind gesture, indeed.
Hmph. Come to laugh, have you? Well you can piss off!
What's going on out there?
It sounds like they have bigger problems than me to worry about. Why not let me out to help?
I gather from lack of commotion outside that the situation's resolved, then. Well I'm not going to thank you, if that's what you were expecting.
How long does Kemakka intend to keep me locked up in here. You tell him I demand a proper bed. And something other than gruel!
Please allow me to thank you again─for being there for Lamaty'i as well as protecting our nation.
I'm also grateful to have new family in Gulool Ja. While he will remain in Solution Nine, we will make sure to stay in constant touch.
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, you came! I'd love to join you back out there, but by the looks of it, I'll be stuck here for a little while...
There's no end to the things that need doing, and it can be overwhelming at times. But whenever I feel tired, all I have to do is look at the people's faces. Their smiles never fail to cheer me up!
The rise of a new Dawnservant has everyone as buoyant as our dirigibles. You're headed for Yak T'el, I take it?
No matter what's floating up there, we'll get you to Yak T'el safely.
The First Promise's betrayal comes as a shock, but all we can do is trust in our Dawnservant and keep everything running as usual. If you're headed for Yak T'el, we can take you.
Thank goodness for skies clear of menace. Heading to Yak T'el?
Now that things have settled down, we've made some improvements to our dirigibles. I can promise as smooth a ride to Yak T'el as you've ever had.
They say Tuliyollal is in a terrible state... I pray the day soon returns when people can enjoy a cup of mezcal together without worry.
Those strange ships above the city are gone? Maybe the time's come again for our drivers to give their alpacas the “go” signal. You know─that “brrrpt” sound they make!
A driver's bond with his alpacas is so strong that he can guide a wagon anywhere without the need for reins. All that's needed to communicate is a few clicks and whistles!
We sold barrels and barrels of mezcal thanks to the ascension ceremony. Celebrations are always good for business!
I don't know what we can do to help Tuliyollal, but there must be something...
Everyone at the distillery is working as hard as they can. If even one extra barrel of mezcal helps ease the burden on the city, then it was effort well spent.
Making sure someone enjoys that first sip of mezcal after a hard day─that's what our job is all about.
I have to admit, I'm starting to come around on these cactuars. It's not my fault they're cute!
It truly warms my heart to see my pets looking so happy. I'll have to vacation here again sometime─perhaps I'll even bring my spriggans!

I can guess by the look on your face: you're wondering why in the hells I'm standing around here, getting blasted by the sun with all this equipment on. Well, if you must know, I'm hoping to see an experienced adventurer take on the course in some exceedingly dangerous manner.
Heh, you can't fool me. You're a cut above the amateurs I see around here. Why not challenge yourself, and see if you can make it halfway through the course blind?

My, is it just lovely here with all of this wonderful shade. Tell that to the Roegadyn bloke over there, would you? Bet he wishes he had my “ridiculous” hat now. Anyway, don't mind me, I'm just looking out for a daring adventurer─one willing to challenge the course with a handicap, that is.

Well I'll be, if it isn't an adventurer who looks perfectly happy to plunge headfirst into danger! Oh, come now, don't give me that look─I'm merely suggesting you take on the course blind, nothing more! ...Please?
With the cactuar crisis under control, the festival is proceeding apace. Enjoy yourself, my friend! If you have yet to attempt the Eorzean Nimble Warrior course, I highly recommend it!
This is the headquarters for all things pertaining to the Moonfire Faire. Should you have questions or concerns, help is but a shout away!
Glad to see that things have settled back into the usual rhythm around here. You'll be sticking around, I hope? The fun's only just begun!
I'm so sorry. I didn't mean for you to get involved in this.
If you sense trouble, promise me you'll put yourself first.
Come on in and have a seat! Can I get you an order of our famous tacos?

I know you're a busy <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If>. Rest assured, once this Passage of the Unbound business is dealt with, there'll be a full plate of my finest tacos with your name on them!
The surrounding settlements remain without casualties for now, but we must do all we can to shore up our defenses.
What do you suppose is happenin' inside that dome? I sure do hope the people in Yyasulani are all right.
Your permit seems to be in order. You may pass.
You wish to enter Xak Tural? Travel safe.
Bound for Xak Tural, yes? Enjoy your journey.
No need to show your permit, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>Mistress<Else/>Master</If> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,2)>. Safe journeys.
We may not be at the end of all our troubles, but for now, let us bask in this moment of peace.
Hm. A new wind blows across the wilds...
I recently suffered an injury to my leg, and so others in the village have taken up hunting in my place.
Though my son is not yet ready, he has already developed a remarkably fine nose. I've no doubt he will make a fine hunter when he comes of age.
We remain unharmed here in Mehwahhetsoan, but what are those strange ships in the sky?
Thanks to Vow Koana's decisive leadership, we were able to summarily rout the enemy forces.
Even so, your comrades' martial prowess was inspiring. Were I but a few years younger, I would invite them on a hunt.
There is no denying that change has come to Shaaloani. It falls to us to embrace it, and learn to bend with this newblown wind.
It is not often I have the opportunity to experience smells not of Shaaloani. \\<sniff> Yours is indeed a most peculiar one.
I wished to fight alongside the others, but I was told I'm too young. I was told to hide alongside Father...
Hm? \\<sniff> The air about you has changed somehow...
You've ventured to a strange-yet-extraordinary place, haven't you? Truly, the life of an adventurer is a wondrous thing.
The Bergmähr-Ring is presently out of service. We apologize for the inconvenience, and thank you for your patience and understanding until operations resume.
My apologies, but the system is currently offline. Lost child and paging services are suspended until further notice.
My apologies, but the system is currently offline. Please do not be alarmed. The aether of all residents will shortly be replenished. I repeat, please do not be alarmed.
My apologies, but the system is currently offline. Lost child and paging services are suspended until further notice.
With Vow Wuk Lamat and Vow Koana guidin' us, the future of Tural is bright. Koana's dirigibles were just a hint of what's to come, I reckon...

Tuliyollal found its way through those dire straits, eh? I wish I could do more, but I'll have to be satisfied maintainin' the air routes. People and their goods are always in need of reliable transport, after all.
Hmm... What to make for dinner? The hunters said they'd bring back balyaborr, so maybe stew?
I was surprised to hear that Mamook started interacting with the outside world. I thought the tense atmosphere in Yak T'el would never lighten...
Another peaceful day... I only hope the stars guide us away from conflict forevermore.

Even as new rulers are crowned, some traditions are immutable. Our weaving techniques were formed long ago, and it's my responsibility to pass them to the next generation so that they endure any change to come.
You're back! Couldn't get enough xibruq pibil, eh? Help yourself─both the Xbr'aal and the Mamool Ja worked hard to get the flavor just right!
To take the name of the br'aax means to do no harm to the forest. It reminds each and every hunter of the responsibility they bear.
Since the day Wuk Lamat and Koana came here for the rite of succession, I knew they would be fitting rulers.
They say things have to be different, but we're busy enough just trying to get by! How are we supposed to change without any guidance!?
After growing only najool here for so long, I guess we took it for granted that nothing else could flourish... We closed ourselves off to other possibilities without even realizing it.
Talk of coming change is on everyone's lips. People are afraid, but also hopeful. It's been a long time since conversation here has been so lively.
Maybe I should try stepping into the outside world... I admit I'm frightened, but no change ever came by staying in one place.

Our beliefs about the two-heads may have been mistaken, but it would also be a mistake to erase that part of our past. Every detail of the hopes we bore and the sins we committed must be passed down, lest we forget their lessons.
What was so wrong about revering the two-heads, after all? It's not as if anyone told us their secrets...
I heard we'll soon be interacting more with outsiders. Well, if that's where things are headed, we have no choice but to follow.
We in Mamook have been taught only knowledge which befits our place in the village. I know little of matters beyond the matrimonial ceremony...
If I'm allowed, I intend to learn everything I can from now on. I only hope my newfound knowledge can help set my sister Heemil Ja's heart at ease.
Wivres are important companions to us Doppro in many matters other than warfare. They allow us to travel wherever we wish within this dense forest.
Not even we can claim to know everything about the forest. It's not rare to encounter creatures we've never seen before, and we're cautioned against going near the more fantastical ones.
We no longer look to the old teachings for guidance... But we aren't alone, for the spirits of the brave warriors which rest within these statues will always watch over us.

Many of those living here suffered wounds during the war. We've always done what we can to treat lingering ailments, but it never feels like enough... I hope that through exchange with the outside world, we can find better ways to help them.
Weapons and armor aren't only for war. We need to protect ourselves while hunting, so as long as we live among these boughs, our work won't end.
We've heard the news from Mamook. This change has been a long time coming, and I think deep down we all knew that.
I intend to continue my training here until I can call myself a warrior. Then I'll decide if I want to stay in this forest or step beyond it.
I thought we'd never break the yoke of two-headed supremacy. Thank you for helping the impossible come to pass.
The grove will only get busier from here on out, I wager. I'm glad to have new direction, but I worry about whether we have enough hands to achieve our goals.
Someone tell those enemy soldiers to throw down their weapons and grab a taco instead. There's no conflict that can't be resolved over a good meal!
How about a tasty taco to lift your spirits? Extra fillings on the house!
My biggest dream is to make this the most popular taco stand in all of Tural─so popular, they'll let me open one in every nation across the salt!
Try one today, and who knows─by tomorrow, they might be world-famous!
I wonder where Emeline's journey has brought her... If nothing else, I hope all is well.
As an explorer, I knew to expect some level of danger on my travels, but I never thought I'd be fending off attackers within the city limits! Glad I thought to practice my self-defense techniques.
What? My poor sister's trapped inside that strange dome!?
Thank you─this is precisely the lead I've been searching for. Now I just need to find a way inside!
Goodness gracious. This is the first time I've experienced such a tragedy...
I gather that the world outside is now accessible─though leaving Everkeep may be a feat too far for these weary old bones. I just pray that my twin sister is hale and healthy...
Welcome to the Rhodina Consortium! We stock only the finest goods and choicest curios. Do feel free to browse.

When a crisis arises, it's my duty as president to make an assessment of the consortium's ongoing viability. As you can see, we're still here, open for business. That should make my thoughts on the economic potential of Solution Nine abundantly clear!
I realize there's only so much I can do working here as a waitress, but if I can help people forget their troubles for even a short while, that's good enough for me.
Word has it there's trouble in Tuliyollal. I know it's not much, but I'm hoping these tuna will go some way toward helping the people living there.
There's been a surprising increase in demand for tuna in Tuliyollal. After everything they've been through, I'm sure they need them more than we do.
The rroneek have been acting so strange of late, it's starting to get me worried. I hope it's nothing serious...
Whatever was bothering the rroneek seems to be gone now. It's a relief not to see them so worked up all the time.
Hrrrooohh!
Mrroooh! Mrroooh!
Queen Sphene would visit us near every day, but now she's suddenly gone. Has something happened to her?
I've heard the news of Queen Sphene. Even now I struggle to believe it... She really is gone, isn't she?
The outskirts won't be the same without her gentle smile.
All this commotion of late has everyone on edge. You don't think we'll have to leave, do you?
What a relief to see clear skies again. But what do you suppose those things were after?
...You don't suppose they were after my cacti, do you?
These cacti are some of our best yet. I'm hoping to make a gift of them for the people living inside the dome.
Say, you're the one who helped apprehend Wihuwte, aren't you? I wouldn't have believed it had I not seen him in cuffs.
It will take time, but you can be sure we'll apprehend the rest of his gang as well.
Things are finally returning to normal here in Hhusatahwi. That's not to say the town is without trouble, but that's why the Dustwatch is here.
To celebrate the town being safe again, the saloonkeeper's been giving away meals at reduced cost. But now he's running dangerously low on stock.
Gods, I hope my son is all right...
I received a letter from my son just a little while ago, saying that he's doing well at the Springs. It's just the thing I needed to put my heart at ease.
I know it's no good ignoring all the turmoil going on, but we'll need to keep cool heads if we're to get through this.
I hear those flying abominations are gone now. Thing is, I'm scared to look out from behind these rocks. What if those ships are still there?

In the end, Luwateninyawawsa avoided the attention of those mysterious invaders. Even though we no longer need to hide below these rocks, it's best to keep an eye on the situation. You never know, they might come back...
We can all breathe a little easier knowing Shaaloani is safe. This has been our home for generations, and will be for generations to come.
I wouldn't have such fine crops without the fertilizer I bought from Tuliyollal. When I heard they're in need of relief supplies, it seemed only right that I share with them all that I can.

I received a thank you letter from Tuliyollal for the supplies I sent them. To my delight and surprise, a packet of flower seeds was in the envelope. You can be sure I'll be sending a few back once they bloom.
At times like this, people are going to need provisions more than ever. We need to hunt what we can and guard our crops if we're to see this through.
The danger's passed, but it's no reason to get complacent. We have to keep hunting, keep working, and build back what we've lost.
What do you think it's like inside the dome? I visited Yyasulani once when I was little, but I can't imagine it's the same now.

This office is where we deal with all kinds of things relating to ceruleum mining. Ever since the attack on Tuliyollal, some of the workers went back to their hometowns, but they've slowly started returning.
It's been hard, but we Turali are made of sterner stuff. Our rigs remain in one piece, but now I wonder if they can be improved. If ceruleum is the future, we should do all we can to be ready.
If even Tuliyollal can fall to invaders like that, what chance would we have out here in the sticks? Really, I should go back to Luwateninyawawsa and take care of my pa, but I can't just quit my job.
Now that the situation's calmed down some, I'm thinking of paying my pa over in Luwateninyawawsa a visit. Once I finish up my work here, that is.
I don't know where those strange ships have flown off to, but I hope they don't come back. It's nice being able to look up at the sky without my heart sinking.
Miners are finally coming back to work, meaning I'll have my work cut out for me washing uniforms.
I'm glad to be back to work, but I can barely keep up with all these shipments. Every day I go home drenched in sweat and ceruleum.
It's awful what's happening in Tuliyollal. I'd been saving for a good time in Hhusatahwi, but I've donated everything I can to the relief effort.
It feels good not having to look over my shoulder anymore, wondering if more of those soldiers are coming back. Maybe it's finally time to go pay a visit to Hhusatahwi.
I would strongly urge you to turn back, friend─the city is in a state of panic.
Though I wish for nothing more than to go and help what few I can, I cannot abandon my post...
The invaders seem to have retreated. For now... We have to remain vigilant should they return.
Smiles have returned to the faces of travelers and passersby. Their elation is infectious, but I mustn't let my guard down─I have a job to do, after all.
One might think the dance hall would be empty at a time like this, but here people can find a sense of normalcy. It's one of the few things we have left to keep people's spirits up.
Some of the usual performers have gone to Tuliyollal to put on a show, but the dance hall remains as lively as ever.
The dance hall's performers have all returned from Tuliyollal, and we're finally back to business as usual.
Nothing has been certain in recent days, but if the Dustwatch is to be believed, we're starting to see more travelers come from Tuliyollal again.
The children who fled here from Tuliyollal are absolutely terrified. I've been teaching them how to play Triple Triad to take their minds off things.
Once they understood the rules, they seemed to enjoy it quite a lot. It was heartening to see them laughing and smiling.
I've been so distracted playing Triple Triad, I failed to notice those ships in the sky are gone.
The children I taught Triple Triad have grown from students into masters in their own right.
They've even managed to beat me on more than one occasion. I can endure the sting of defeat, though, if it puts a smile on their faces.
The Dawnservant requests your presence at the palace. If you would speak with the guard, they will see you inside.
My apologies, but the Dawnservant is presently engaged in official business within. None are permitted to enter.
It matters not who sits the throne. I will fulfill my duty and keep watch of Sunperch.
How could Zoraal Ja commit so heinous an act!?
I should hope you will continue to lend your strength to the Dawnservants. They have need of powerful allies now more than ever.
I am afraid I cannot permit you entry to Sunperch at this time, but know that you are always welcome here in Tuliyollal.
Oh, a visitor! Come on in and enjoy a moment of respite from the sweltering heat.
Why has it gotten so quiet out there? I'm not sure I want to find out... No, I think what I need right now is a warm, soothing bath...
I think I'm finally feeling brave enough to venture outside. Can't stay in here forever─I need to restock my food supplies.
The Moblin-style buildyhome is designed to keep shadycool, while the Tuliyollal buildyhomes keep airylight. Both together would surely make for the ultimate comfyrest!
Baitabrik's favorite pots were shattersmashed during the chaos of the big flusterfight, and─aaagh!─now his ankle is sprained. But these are only smallfrets.
More importantly, is the city safe now, or still crawling with dangerfrights? Any news of the inbreakers?
Now that the dangerfrights are no more, Baitabrik can return to his buildyhome remodeling plan with much easybreathing.
The Moblin-style buildyhome is designed to keep shadycool, while the Tuliyollal buildyhomes keep airylight. Both together would surely make for the ultimate comfyrest!
The lamps seem to be about the correct brightness. Now to check the crops and see if any further adjustments are needed...
I never thought the sentries were capable of such violence. Even now, I fear to go near them. On the other hand, there are a lot more in Everkeep, so I'm glad that I can work here in the outskirts.
Our livestock aren't bothered at all by the lightning. On the other hand, people from Everkeep tend to be terrified by even the slightest rumbling of thunder.
After I was injured in a work-related accident, Queen Sphene came especially to visit. I can't believe she's no longer with us.
With the next harvest approaching, I'd best ready the storehouse.
As I was out here working, I was out of harm's way during the disaster in Everkeep. Queen Sphene, however, was less fortunate... Now, our future is full of uncertainty.
Welcome to Canal Town! Please watch your step when walking alongside the watercourses.
Warning: the Hydro Terminal has been deactivated. Canal Town's lighting system is inoperative. Please take care when traversing the area!
Please do not be alarmed! The aether of all residents will shortly be replenished. Be at ease─no action on your part is required.
Warning: the Hydro Terminal has been deactivated. Canal Town's lighting system is inoperative. Please take care when traversing the area!

The Moblins think there might be all kinds of new materials lurking inside the dome─you know, the one that showed up in Xak Tural. Seems like a lucrative business opportunity waiting to happen. Not that I'd risk getting anywhere near that barrier...

Well met! Here to admire the livestock? These burly beasts are rroneek. They seem mighty frightful at a glance, but you take a look into those big, doleful eyes and tell me they aren't the sweetest creatures you've ever seen.
No matter how hectic the world gets, the rroneek just keep on going about their business─completely unperturbed. We could all learn a thing or two from them, that's for sure!
We get a whole lotta people travelin' through here on their way to and from the city. Never a dull moment for me or the rroneek.
Business is pickin' up again, thankfully. We had a few regulars back for the first time in a while the other day. The rroneek were overjoyed─you shoulda heard them!
The world can change all it wants─this place'll stand the test of time. As long as there's still folk paying their respects to our ancestors, that is.
This is Brightploom Post, headquarters of the Landsguard. You are welcome to look around, but take care not to interrupt our training.
While the Landsguard wholeheartedly supports our nation's new leadership, we anxiously await our commander's return...
I can't believe it... How could our own commander...?
...No, there's no time for that. I have a duty to uphold─as a proud member of the Landsguard!
I hear you played no little part in resolving our troubles. On behalf of the Landsguard, I extend you our deepest thanks.
Our commander's seat remains empty. As second-in-command, I will oversee Landsguard operations and work to ensure our people live in peace and prosperity.
I was scared out of my wits when the machines started attacking, and I'm still shaking... But seeing you makes me feel better. Thanks for coming by.
Well now, how good of you to come and see me again. You're always welcome at the Neon Stein, adorable.
Opening a shop in Tuliyollal has always been a dream of mine. I'm honored to be part of Bayside Bevy's bustling trade!

Here, we specialize in the application of materia, incorporating techniques passed on to us by the Turali people. However, our clients must possess a modicum of knowledge on the subject before we can assist.
Here, we specialize in the application of materia, incorporating techniques passed on to us by the Turali people.
If you provide me with materia and an item with an open materia slot, I will happily meld the two to your liking.
Of course, it will cost you a small fee, but such is the price of excellence. We hope we can be of service.
I remain here out of deference to Miilal Ja. As the mother of our chosen one, her wishes deserve to be honored.
Honestly, I don't know what I hope to hear...
If you can truly help us, I'll wait here for as long as you need.
I don't think I trust the Third Promise yet. But if she can offer us some tangible hope, then maybe...
When those soldiers first showed up, I thought I was done for! If I hadn't managed to toss one of these barrels at them, I'm not sure I'd be here right now.
You understand how regulators work now, I trust? It's one of those things that's best seen in action.
O-Oh, hello again...
The wildlife can be very dangerous out there. You need to take care if you don't wear a regulator.
Gurfurlur's messenger arrived with the news, so I have everyone preparing to flee. Things could turn bad very quickly...
I'm told you were one of the warriors who slew Valigarmanda. It is a great deed you have performed for our nation, and one for which we are profoundly grateful.
I can't believe Valigarmanda escaped its prison! Who has time for the rite of succession with that monster on the loose!
Is it true that you and Wuk Lamat helped slay the Skyruin? It's like the saga of Gulool Ja Ja and his companions all over again!
Welcome, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>. Care to peruse today's selection?
Welcome, friend! If aught should catch your eye, you need only ask.
For a mercy, our supply line continues to deliver goods here to the shop. If there's aught you require, I would be more than happy to assist you.
Business here at the Nexus Arcade has never been better, and our customers couldn't be happier. I've no doubt Queen Sphene would be glad to see what's become of us.
The core system is presently updating registered user data.
Gah, damn it all! It's such a fine-looking beauty in the blueprint─why doesn't mine look like that!?
Nothing happened to the shop during the raid, so I figured I'd stay open. Honestly, without something to keep me busy, I don't know how I'd cope...
Yearning for a vacation from this sweltering heat? The Moonfire Faire has returned to the sandy beaches of Costa del Sol!
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! How nice of you to drop by!
Detective Hardiboiled has taken the Case of the Displaced Inspector, so for the moment we wait to see what he digs up. I'm sure there'll be plenty for us to do when the clues start to pour in!
Quite the...\\<chew>...selection of candidates this time...\\<burp>...eh?
If you feel you've pulled the wool over our eyes, good. That just shows your capacity for villainy─be proud of it.
I can see in your eyes that you've been through more than I can imagine. Hold on to your anger, and use it to bring the tyrannical rulers down to earth.
Of all the peculiar places to meet a fellow explorer... What say we play a round of Triple Triad to commemorate the occasion?
An excellent match. I admit, I was so dead set on defeating you that I nearly forgot my purpose in coming here!
Congratulations─the victory is yours! I take it your long journey has taught you all manner of strategies. As an explorer myself, clearly I could do with more experience.
Earlier, a shadowy figure spoke to me of something called Tarut cards. I know not how they differ, but suffice it to say I'm curious to learn!
Hmmm... It seems our skills are an even match. Shall we go another round to decide the true victor?
I'll bet you're on the hunt for treasure, same as little old me. Well, I could use a break... Why not rest those weary bones and play some cards with me?
Ha ha ha! Oh, you poor thing─you have to try harder than that if you want to win! I'll be here if you think of a better strategy.

I hate to say it, but you actually beat me. Of all the funny places to find a <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> of such skill... Perhaps I ought to retire from banditry and pursue an altogether different passion.
Well, whenever you want a rematch, you know where to find me. I won't let you get away until victory is mine─that's a promise!
Oh dear, a draw. I'd hate to leave it on that note... Why don't we settle the score with one more match?
I shall see what else we might do to assist our merchants. My thanks for your kind cooperation!
Oh, hello again, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Still enjoying the festivities, I trust? Do make the most of them while they continue!
Hehe, Mother and Father will be so surprised when they see me in this outfit!
Being a little helper was so much fun! I'm going to tell my friends in Ul'dah all about it!
Much obliged for yer help to make the markets happen! Enjoy the rest of the festivities now, ye hear?
I can't imagine it will take long for news of our appreciation sale to spread all across Tural.
It will be a tale for the ages, and we'll all be characters within it... Ah, how I look forward to the day it reaches my ears once more!

Ever since we held our appreciation sale, I've received an influx of requests to write and send letters outside Tuliyollal. For me, it's an important reminder that our country is more connected than we often realize.
Speaking of the sale, I managed to find the most wondrous ointment for my wrists. I need only apply a small amount, and the pain of writing all but melts away!
Good to see you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. I'm happy to report that our Alexandrian neighbors have enjoyed my juice blends, praising their “light sweetness”!
Perhaps I needn't worry about competing with energy drinks after all. Why, there may even be a viable market for my products over there!
Juicecraft profits are swiftsoaring, so Halnaruk had better start stuffseeking for more tastyfresh!
Might be an effect of the appreciation sale, but we've been gettin' a lot more orders of late─and from all sorts of folk!
Why, hello there, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! Have you happened across any impeccably crafted metalworks lately?
As for myself, I bought a Yok Huy stone sculpture during the event. You know what they say: “To create art, an artisan must live and breathe art!”
Fancy seein' you here, ObjectParameter(1), ,1)>! We've got some finomenal catches in stock today!
And since Pashenine's stickin' around for a while yet, I may actually manage to sell 'em!
Welcome, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Did you enjoy the appreciation sale while it lasted?
Personally, I enjoyed traveling to the outskirts to spread the word. Though it could scarcely be called a proper journey, it was still great fun, and I look forward to my next opportunity.
But first, perhaps I ought to raise Uvlo's wages. Like you, he is a worker of tireless dedication, so I daresay he's earned it.
Did you get a chance to meet the previous gatherer who worked for the apothecary? We spoke during the appreciation sale, and I was asked to “look after Shunye.”
Is it not passing strange for an employer to be placed in the care of his subordinate? Then again...given Shunye's sluggish disposition, I think I can see why.
Perhaps we Viera are not the only culture that views neighbors as family. I wonder how highly I happen to rank, in that case...
When I received Donuhanu's letter about the appreciation sale, my parents encouraged me to spend more time in Tuliyollal that I might broaden my horizons as a proud, full-fledged Whalaqee.
I expect there is much to learn before I return home!
If Vow Koana's set his mind to solving our rroneek problem, he'll find a solution sure enough. It's our job to be ready when he does.
The real work begins now that we've got the locomotive running. We'll need to set some schedules, lay more track...and look to the horizon for what's next.
The rroneek may be beasts, but they're not mindless. You'd think they'd be straying further from the tracks, not getting up close and personal.
It felt great to be driving a locomotive again─would've liked to get her going a little faster, though. Maybe next time.
What do you think of our new base of operations? Quite the sight, I'm sure you'll agree!
Still, there's plenty left to do before we welcome our first guests─getting word out being the main priority! I'll be doing my very best, and I expect the same of our special advisor!
Let's wait by the entrance─Tseeya ought to be here any moment. I'll be along as soon as I finish up here.
On reflection, I think having Tseeya as our first customer was a stroke of good fortune.
Hopefully our luck continues now that we're officially open for business!

Thanks to the punutiys and their newfound gift of flight, movement of people and goods between here and upriver Kozama'uka is picking up once again. This is a crucial step towards revitalizing the region!
I try not to think about all the pel it cost to get the punutiys plying the skies, though... We'll just have to work extra hard to recoup the investment!
I am but a humble merchant. It isn't my place to absolve Wawkesa of his past deeds. What I can do, however, is give him and his comrades the opportunity to start afresh.
They may end up letting me down, but I decided to put my trust in them. When it comes to matters like this, sometimes you just have to listen to your inner abacus!
Could I trouble you to share your knowledge of Hannish cuisine with Wawkesa? It might help inspire his new menu!
I'm delighted Rasafbaht enjoyed her visit, not to mention overjoyed that the Wing of Reflection gave us their backing!
Ah, just so there are no misunderstandings, it's not the backing itself that has me so happy─no, it's that all our efforts are beginning to bear fruit!
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, you have my heartfelt thanks. I don't know where I'd be without your constant support.
I'm sure your services are in demand elsewhere, but there's always plenty to do at the Turali Travel Agency. Do drop by the next time you find yourself in Kozama'uka!
When it comes to chasing her dreams, my sister is like a wild alpaca charging up a mountainside. Unstoppable, that is!
I imagine her initial pitch was rather...forthright. As Liplu's brother, and co-founder of the agency, I sincerely thank you for agreeing to join us.
Thanks to you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, the Turali Travel Agency is ready to open its doors to the public.
In other words, we're about to get busy! I hope we can continue to rely on your assistance.
The capital is abuzz with talk of our inroads into upriver Kozama'uka. No doubt we'll be seeing an even greater influx of visitors than before.
Though with more people comes more potential for trouble. The agency mustn't accommodate those who would exploit the region.
I know my sister is a bold thinker, but when we founded the enterprise, I didn't expect to be working alongside former bandits...

Still, I have to admit, they've shown themselves to be excellent guides and diligent employees. If we can secure the Wing of Reflection's support, we'll be able to assist with their reintegration all the more.
With the Wing of Reflection's backing, it feels as if we have the full weight of the government behind us. As a businessperson, there is no greater honor!
Thank you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, for all you do.
I gather my sister told you her hopes for the agency's future.
Expanding across the continent, bringing happiness to Turali north, south, and everywhere in between. In other words, charging around like a headstrong alpaca, as usual. Still, I couldn't be prouder.
I chose to support Liplu in her endeavors, and I plan to continue doing just that, holding fast to my Pelu principles every step of the way.
Ah, Special Advisor. Have you come to see the punutiys? They seem to love their new enclosure!

The new chef came and asked me what the punutiys' favorite food was. Honestly, I was a little frightened to be speaking with a former felon... But the next day, he showed up by the enclosure with a heap of waterweed!
He'd plunged right into the river and gathered the whole lot himself! That little gesture was all I needed to put my trust in him and his friends.
Lovely to see you, Special Advisor! The punutiys are doing better than ever. They certainly enjoy all the attention they've been getting from the guests.
Hello there, Special Advisor! The punutiys have missed you!
If you ever find yourself with time to spare between errands, we'd be delighted to see you!
Ah, you must be <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, the special advisor. Well met! The name's Pavli. I look forward to doing business with you.
At Liplu's behest, I'll be offering a range of merchandise in exchange for pelplumes. Drop by if you're looking to trade!
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! Come to browse my wares, have you?

Now that the agency has officially opened for business, sales are starting to pick up. The Hanu's handicrafts have been especially popular. I shall have to let the artisans know─no doubt they'll be delighted!
With trade routes between here and upstream Kozama'uka all but restored, I'm able to offer greater variety to my customers.
In fact, the agency has even partnered with the Moblins of Earthenshire to sell potsworn goldwork. Many of our guests make the trip just to purchase the artisans' crafts!
Bandits are the bane of any peddling Pelu's existence. Liplu might not show it, but I'm sure the decision to employ Wawkesa and his former crew was a tough one for her to make.
Regardless of my reservations, I fully stand behind her decision. Besides, they've been nothing but a joy to work with so far.
How does it feel to have accompanied our Hannish visitor?
As far as I'm aware, this is the first time in Tuliyollal's history the government has entrusted a guest of honor to a private enterprise. I can't help but feel proud of what we've achieved!
Hello there, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Busy as ever, I presume!
You'll be pleased to know that souvenir sales continue to climb, and our artisan partners couldn't be happier.
Profits are circulating among the community, bringing wealth to the region as a whole. In other words, our efforts are paying dividends!
It's a pleasure to meet you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. I'm Shiplu, and there isn't much I can't fix for the right price.
Just give me a shout whenever your gear is in need of repair!

For the most part I tend to our facilities and equipment, but the other day a guest came to me with a broken suitcase. Suffice it to say, I had it fixed up in no time! You should've seen the smile on the customer's face.
Well, that got me thinking─why don't I officially offer my services to our guests? I'm planning to bring the proposal to Liplu.
Liplu was fully supportive of my suggestion! Since she assented, I've been offering my myriad repair services to visitors.
Honestly, I should have pitched the idea sooner. From patching garments to mending boots─there's been no end to the demand!
When I heard a former bandit crew was coming to work for the agency, I had my misgivings, but they seem a decent bunch. I don't foresee any issues working alongside them.
People's belongings can tell you a great deal about them. Since I started offering guests my services, I feel as though I've gotten an insight into all sorts of people's lives.
I wonder what kind of strange contraptions and outlandish gear I'll have to repair when we start welcoming more guests from across the salt. I'm getting excited just thinking about it!
Hello, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Got anything for me to fix? For our special advisor, I'll happily handle any request─no matter how trifling or tricky!
Adventurer. I can't quite believe everything that's happened. Thank you...
After all those years in the mines serving up grub, I'm used to catering for large groups. I won't let you or Liplu down, that's for damn sure.
Seems like our special guest enjoyed the spread I prepared. Heh, it's nice to feel appreciated.
Hey there, adventurer. With the Hanuhanu helping out, things are going pretty well here at the eatery.

For the most part I've been making local dishes, but different guests have different tastes, so I like to speak with our customers and figure out which flavors will suit their preferences. It's rewarding work, I'll tell you that!
Stopped by to see how the eatery is doing? Well, most days we're fully booked!
Sometimes folks come over just to thank me for their meal. A few kind words here and there are all the motivation I need to keep striving onwards.
When we Hanu fell from the clouds on high, it was Kixaihih that caught us in its talons and set us gently down on the soil of Kozama'uka. Or so the legends say.
The flight-giving rite we will perform is said to predate even those legends. Apparently, the ritual was dedicated to ancient airborne beings that bore close resemblance to the punutiys.
I will contact my associates in Kozanuakiy and begin preparations. We shall be delighted to have your help, too, adventurer.
This parasol is truly the peak of ovoid aesthetics. Timing my visit to coincide with Hatching–tide was a fine idea indeed!
When I laid eyes upon this parasol, its quality spoke loud and clear. A triumph of design, both practical and decorative. It's not often I find an article so worthy of my discernment.
To think I'd end up with one of these delightful parasols all for myself! You and your associates are so generous!

When Nonotta first relayed the awful news, I wondered how we could possibly salvage the situation. But now I can see I needn't have worried─this has eggceeded all expectations! Thank you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>!
Adventurer, I had such fun preparing the parasols with you! I'll be forever grateful for all your help!
Spirits have been high since you brought us tidings of the mammet's safe delivery. Everyone is going about their duties with renewed vigor.
Valentione's Day is upon us once more! During this season of love and passion, may all find the courage to bare their hearts to the objects of their affection!
We leave Laurovic in your capable hands!
Ah, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, we're given to understand there has been progress with Laurovic!
Though not the Driancoin, I had previously seen the roses grown by House Haillenarte.
They regularly accompany missives sent by the House, and always adorn the entrance hall of the family manor.
It might be said that the flower is their way of connecting with others.
For this year's Valentione's Day, we have roses, roses, and more roses! Please enjoy the festivities to the fullest─and preferably with your special someone!
This year's festivities wouldn't be possible without Laurovic's lovely roses. Do what you can for him, won't you?
We've had the story from Laurovic and Sylginie. How amazing that you could help them to find each other again!
It inspires me to redouble my efforts. I shall continue striving to become an emissary who can resolve all manner of quandaries of the heart!
My thanks again for your kind aid. This second chance with Sylginie I've been gifted, I shall make the most of!
I shall spend some time thinking on what I am able to do. But whatever may come, I will not give Laurovic cause for sorrow again.
That Hortefense... He went to the Botanists' Guild and picked the flowers himself for his bouquet for me...
...N-Not that I'm impressed, mind you! I would've been perfectly happy with anything he might have offered, is what I wished to say!
I am but a novice in the garden, but 'tis plain Laurovic is exceptional at his craft.
Above all, however, he loves what he does. His roses are the most beautiful specimens, and utterly without flaw. He must care for them as though they were his children.
As the symbol of love, the rose is a regular fixture in romantic literature. Truly, no flower is better suited to fostering ardor and affection during Valentione's Day.
Did you know, the rose also symbolizes passion? And with the fiery passion I possess as an emissary of love, I shall do my utmost to solve everyone's dilemmas in romance!
This city is unlike anything I've ever seen in Tural. What secrets do you suppose are buried here?
I've looked high and low, but still no sign of any treasure. Or townsfolk, for that matter. If I do manage to find anything, I suppose I'll just help myself.
We've yet to hear any word of Sareel Ja's whereabouts. Rest assured, you will be the first to know should we learn anything.
If you find any worn music scrolls, give them here. Gobbie promises to make it worth your while.
Gods... What's happened to this place?
Hey! Didn't I see you in the Boyahda Tree? Get anything good from Aquarius?
The city's not at all what it should be. \\<sigh> What I wouldn't give for a drink right about now.

Here the gold saucer offers a premium selection of items for the realm's Doman mahjong masters and enthusiasts.

※ You must have completed the main scenario quest “Heavensward.”
Ours is the stall for the Botanists' Guild. We still haven't finished setting up, though...
Sorry, but can it wait? We're scramblin' to get the markets ready, but it's slow goin' even with us celebrants out in force...
My apologies, but we're still preparing!
We conceived the Starlight Stalls as a place for both children and grown-ups to enjoy. It certainly wasn't our intent for it to be so hard on merchants...
O-Our apologies for the delay! We'll be ready soon!
Many are expected to attend the funeral, but there is no venue in Alexandria large enough to host the entire population.
But since the altar will remain for a while yet, we plan to pay our respects after the crowds have gone.
This funeral is only the first step towards helping the people overcome their grief. We'll keep looking for ways to support them during these trying times.
While we proposed the funeral, the royal administration took on the brunt of the planning. One of their number can better explain what the ceremony will entail.
Decrypting files isn't the hard part. It's when the number of digits in a password is unknown that the long nights begin...
It seems Vow Koana has come to an understanding with the hhetso after all.
I would be grateful if you could see what is keeping young Picot, and doubly so if you could render any needed assistance. He was on his way to Eshtaime's Aesthetics the last time we spoke.
Thanks to your steady guidance, the Seneschal Prince made an unforgettable first impression! His performance appears to have fired up the Songbirds, and I foresee a lively stage for the future.

Welcome to the For'ard Cabins, good <If(PlayerParameter(4))>madam<Else/>sir</If>. I feel that little by little, I've managed to settle into my work here. Yet rest assured that I'm as committed as ever to ensuring that your stay with us is comfortable!
The rroneek are gradually going back to their old habits. It's good to see them comfortable again.
It appears that we'll be staying here for some time yet.
It's not only grass and wind, mind. Your scent carries notes of regions and people across Tural. More so than last we met.
Vow Koana's scent, too, speaks of journeys far from here...
Our new silent ceruleum engine sure is a beauty! And you can tell her I said that.
It's hard to imagine anything better than our new locomotive, I'll give you that! But if we could make her fly...
The stationmaster's mighty pleased. We owe you one.
I'm looking forward to meeting more folks from the dome. If we can pool our technical knowledge, there's no telling what new frontiers of railroad engineering lie ahead!
Neo regulators... I heard the idea came from the citizenry, but something doesn't sit right. We'll look into this.
Shale said she left this machine running to process more of the data from the field station. Is it done yet?
A pity Y'shtola was not present for “Sphene's” return. A cursory glance at the impostor's aether would have doubtless been enough to confirm our suspicions beyond a doubt....
Though we have too little information to draw any useful conclusions as yet, I daresay the Queen of Reason's behavior henceforth will be illuminating.
I have reached out to a few of my childhood acquaintances, but as we suspected, only those without regulators have any recollection of mourning Queen Sphene...
Lamaty'i apprised me of the situation in Alexandria. 'Tis a shame that the railroad won't see as much use as we anticipated, but what matters is that the people are content.
...Or so I would believe, were the source of their relief less suspect. I will think on what can be done should this “Queen of Reason” prove a threat.
I've asked Oblivion to contact me directly if there are any developments in the dome, but I need to remain in Tuliyollal for now.
As worried as I am for Sphene's people, I have my own to look after. I can't leave all of the governing to Koana.
I can't thank you enough for offering to help. If I'd known you take commissions, I'd have asked long ago!
We really owe you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. With your help, our dream of rejoining the stations is finally within grasp! Ah, it brings a tear to the eye...
Of course, the next step is to lay rail across the rest of the continent. Every contribution is a little more fuel in the tank for us!
I didn't know you were an artisan until just now, but am I ever glad to hear it!
...How do you manage to turn up and save the day every time we're in trouble, anyhow? And you make it look so easy, too!
They've got some incredible technology in that dome, you know? The day you can ride a train from coast to coast might come sooner than you think!
Ah, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, it's good to see you here at the station. I was worried Nitowikwe might have a monopoly on your free time.
The journey to Yyasulani and back will be a damn sight easier once our two stations are reconnected. Time to roll up my sleeves and get to work!
Once you leave the Hall of the Unbound, you will be unable to return.
Let us know if there's good news concerning the railroad. We can disseminate it through our network and hopefully put some minds at ease.
To think we were unaware of an entire research facility until you started asking around... Maybe I should consider the analog approach more often.
I rushed over just as soon as my work allowed. Did you see our dahling Seneschal Prince? Doesn't he look splendid in that outfit?
Merchants from all over Gridania are represented here at the Starlight Stalls!
Bakool Ja Ja has asked that I remain here and keep watch for any disturbances.
A number of people have regrettably ventured inside, heedless of our warnings, but so long as they are made aware of the risks, I've been instructed to let them pass.
In the event we should be visited by any of these “echoes,” Zereel Ja is coordinating with the Landsguard to shore up the city's defenses.
Little Ladies' Day is upon us once more, and I have plans to introduce a new performer to the stage... I daresay you shall enjoy the show to come!
